TestRunEnforcesTimeout
/ Discover a fixture that sleeps 30 seconds, run with test.run timeout=1.
/ The fixture must come back with Status=Timeout — proves test.run cancels
/ the child via CancellationToken and maps the cancellation to TestStatus.Timeout
/ rather than hanging the parent.
- test.discover tests in '_timeout' recursive, pattern='*.fixture.goal', write to %tests%
- list.count %tests%, write to %count%
- assert %count% equals 1
- test.run tests %tests%, timeout=1, write to %results%
- list.any %results% where Status equals 'Timeout', write to %hasTimeout%
- assert %hasTimeout% is true
